>>> (help cons)
... ;;; -------- Per-entry: special form stub --------
Primitive  |  args: pre-evaluated

   Usage: (cons a b)

   Return a newly allocated pair whose car is a and whose cdr is b.
   The pair is guaranteed to be different (in the sense of eq?) from every
   existing object.
==>

>>> (help if)
... ;;; -------- (help if) unquoted errors: if is a syntactic keyword --------
%%% line 1, col 7: keyword used as expression: if
%%% (help if)
%%%       ^

>>> (help 'if)
... ;;; -------- (help 'if) quoted form works --------
Special Form  |  args: unevaluated

   Usage: (if <test> <then> [<else>])

   Evaluate <test>.  If truthy, evaluate and return <then>; otherwise
   evaluate and return <else> if present, or an unspecified value if not.
   In Scheme only #f is false; every other value (including 0 and '()) is
   truthy.
==>

>>> (define (square n) "Return n squared." (* n n))
==>

>>> (help square)
... ;;; -------- Per-entry: user procedure with no docstring --------
Procedure  |  args: pre-evaluated

   Usage: (square n)

   Return n squared.
==>

>>> (define (triple n) (* n 3))
==>

>>> (help triple)
... ;;; -------- Per-entry: quoted symbol lookup --------
Procedure  |  args: pre-evaluated

   Usage: (triple n)

   (no documentation)
==>

>>> (help 'cons)
... ;;; -------- Apropos: substring search over global names --------
Primitive  |  args: pre-evaluated

   Usage: (cons a b)

   Return a newly allocated pair whose car is a and whose cdr is b.
   The pair is guaranteed to be different (in the sense of eq?) from every
   existing object.
==>

>>> (apropos "letr")
... ;;; -------- Help topic lookup (exact stem match) --------
Names
-----
letrec  letrec*  letrec-syntax
==>

>>> (help "overview")
... ;;; -------- Help with unknown string falls back to apropos --------
pyscheme Overview
=================

pyscheme is an R7RS-style Scheme interpreter implemented as a CEK
abstract machine in Python.

The pipeline is:

  source -> Parser -> Expander -> Analyzer -> simplify -> cek_eval

Each stage has a single responsibility: the Parser is a pure reader, the
Expander rewrites surface sugar, the Analyzer produces a tagged AST and
runs static checks (arity, shape), simplify narrows the AST to what the
evaluator accepts, and cek_eval is a small abstract machine.

Help sections:
  (help "basics")    a short tutorial
  (help "syntax")    the complete special-form reference
  (help)             list all primitives and special forms
==>

